{"id":"172338516139198_1093398527366521","from":{"name":"Mohamed Moshrif","id":"1235868066468537"},"message":"Any ruby experts here that can answer that question:\n\n","story":"Mohamed Moshrif shared a link to the group: Egyptian Geeks.","story_tags":{"0":[{"id":"1235868066468537","name":"Mohamed Moshrif","type":"user","offset":0,"length":15}],"44":[{"id":"172338516139198","name":"Egyptian Geeks","type":"group","offset":44,"length":14}]},"picture":"https://fbexternal-a.akamaihd.net/safe_image.php?d=AQBBxyEJXpSqBr8p&w=130&h=130&url=http%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sstatic.net%2Fstackoverflow%2Fimg%2Fapple-touch-icon%402.png%3Fv%3D73d79a89bded%26a&cfs=1&_nc_hash=AQA5Q7_FL6tqp531","link":"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/35859239/calling-js-function-from-erb-file","name":"Calling js function from erb file","caption":"stackoverflow.com","description":"I have an erb file that is creating a table. Something like this: <td>Option 1</td> <td>Option 2</td> I have a javascript function called Foo() placed inside the applicat...","icon":"https://www.facebook.com/images/icons/post.gif","actions":[{"name":"Comment","link":"https://www.facebook.com/172338516139198/posts/1093398527366521"},{"name":"Like","link":"https://www.facebook.com/172338516139198/posts/1093398527366521"},{"name":"Report Post to Admin","link":"https://www.facebook.com/groups/egyptian.geeks/members/"}],"privacy":{"value":"","description":"","friends":"","allow":"","deny":""},"type":"link","status_type":"shared_story","created_time":"2016-03-08T05:01:05+0000","updated_time":"2016-03-08T09:22:35+0000","is_hidden":false,"is_expired":false,"comments":{"data":[{"created_time":"2016-03-08T06:57:33+0000","from":{"name":"Nabil Naeem","id":"10158708930020157"},"message":"I think that calling a script file from an element is not really a best practice.\nYou should \"only\" include the javascript before/after the DOM is loaded.\nBut you may try a jquery binding on page load.\nOr is there any special reason behind your approach?","can_remove":false,"like_count":0,"user_likes":false,"id":"1093433704029670"},{"created_time":"2016-03-08T08:01:49+0000","from":{"name":"Ahmed El Gabri","id":"10158299136875582"},"message":"To make it work you need to replace the <script> tag with a <span on<event>=\"foo();\"> foo</span>. \n\nThat being said, inline scripts & putting everything in the global scope like this, is very bad & will cause lots of issue performance wise and maintainability wise. \n\nYou should have this function called by an external script. \n\nLike this. <span class=\"js-foo\"> foo</span> & then in your JS file you should attach the event on the element with class \"js-foo\".","can_remove":false,"like_count":3,"user_likes":false,"id":"1093450000694707"},{"created_time":"2016-03-08T09:20:36+0000","from":{"name":"Hosam Aly","id":"1348336588561390"},"message":"I think you want to call your JS function when the user chooses that option. If that's the case then use Ahmed El Gabri's suggestion.\n\nBut I don't think your HTML structure is correct. It looks like you want either a <select> with <option> tags or <a> tags on these options.","can_remove":false,"like_count":0,"user_likes":false,"id":"1093472064025834"}],"paging":{"cursors":{"before":"WTI5dGJXVnVkRjlqZAFhKemIzSTZANVEE1TXpRek16Y3dOREF5T1RZAM01Eb3hORFUzTkRJd01qVTAZD","after":"WTI5dGJXVnVkRjlqZAFhKemIzSTZANVEE1TXpRM01qQTJOREF5TlRnek5Eb3hORFUzTkRJNE9ETTIZD"}}}}